 is included in a budget plan.","pos":[3579,3755]},{"content":"Specific fields define the behavior of the budget cost element.","pos":[3758,3821]},{"content":"Each budget cost element is assigned a budget cost type of <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Earning<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Benefit<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Taxes<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>, or <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Other<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept>.","pos":[3822,3931],"source":" Each budget cost element is assigned a budget cost type of **Earning**, **Benefit**, **Taxes**, or **Other**."},{"content":"The budget cost types are primarily used to calculate totals.","pos":[3932,3993]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Forecast position override<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> value specifies whether the amounts on the element can be modified on the forecast position.","pos":[3994,4121],"source":" The **Forecast position override** value specifies whether the amounts on the element can be modified on the forecast position."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Allocation method<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field is used when a forecast position is added to a budget plan.","pos":[4122,4213],"source":" The **Allocation method** field is used when a forecast position is added to a budget plan."},{"content":"You can split the cost amount onto separate budget plan lines that have different dates, on a monthly, quarterly, weekly, or biweekly basis.","pos":[4214,4354]},{"content":"By selecting a start date, you assign the cost as a single amount on the start date that is set on the forecast position.","pos":[4355,4476]},{"content":"The calculation of the budget cost element’s cost amount uses effective dates to enable the same cost element to be used in different periods.","pos":[4479,4621]},{"content":"A single main account is assigned in each period, together with a percentage or annual amount that indicates the cost amount.","pos":[4622,4747]},{"content":"A budget cost element can use a percentage of other cost elements or an annual amount, but not both.","pos":[4748,4848]},{"content":"You can also specify an annual limit.","pos":[4849,4886]},{"content":"If the cost element is based on a percentage, you must specify the budget cost elements that are used as the basis for the calculation.","pos":[4889,5024]},{"pos":[5026,5037],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Example<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Example**"},{"content":"Jodi’s organization is providing a training allowance of 5 percent of an employee’s base pay.","pos":[5040,5133]},{"content":"Jodi wants to create a budget cost element for this cost.","pos":[5134,5191]},{"content":"She creates a new budget cost element and assigns the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Benefit<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> budget cost type.","pos":[5192,5275],"source":" She creates a new budget cost element and assigns the **Benefit** budget cost type."},{"content":"Jodi doesn't want managers to change the amount of the benefit.","pos":[5277,5340]},{"content":"Therefore, she selects <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Do not allow cost changes<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Forecast position override<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> field.","pos":[5341,5438],"source":" Therefore, she selects **Do not allow cost changes** in the **Forecast position override** field."},{"content":"The organization wants this cost to be assigned evenly to each month.","pos":[5439,5508]},{"content":"Therefore, Jodi selects <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Quarterly<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Allocation method<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> field.","pos":[5509,5582],"source":" Therefore, Jodi selects **Quarterly** in the **Allocation method** field."},{"content":"Next, Jodi adds a cost calculation line, sets the dates and a main account, and enters <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>5.00<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> as the percentage.","pos":[5585,5699],"source":"Next, Jodi adds a cost calculation line, sets the dates and a main account, and enters **5.00** as the percentage."},{"content":"Her organization has a cap of $5,000 per year for this benefit.","pos":[5700,5763]},{"content":"Therefore, Jodi enters that amount as the annual limit.","pos":[5764,5819]},{"content":"Finally, Jodi adds all the earning cost elements that are used for base pay as calculation bases.","pos":[5822,5919]},{"content":"Her budget cost element is now ready to be used.","pos":[5920,5968]},{"pos":[5974,5993],"content":"Compensation groups","linkify":"Compensation groups","nodes":[{"content":"Compensation groups","pos":[0,19]}]},{"content":"Compensation groups can be used to group forecast position that have similar compensation attributes.","pos":[5995,6096]},{"content":"They can also be used to define a forecast position’s earnings and annual increases, and to assign a set of common budget cost elements.","pos":[6097,6233]},{"content":"A basic function of compensation groups is to assign a set of budget cost elements to a forecast position.","pos":[6236,6342]},{"content":"Therefore, compensation groups can be used to add common costs, such as benefit plans and taxes.","pos":[6343,6439]},{"content":"A manager who is creating a forecast position doesn't have to know all the cost elements that must be added.","pos":[6440,6548]},{"content":"Instead, the cost elements can be added when the compensation group is selected.","pos":[6549,6629]},{"content":"The elements are added to the compensation group setup on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Budget cost elements<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab.","pos":[6630,6721],"source":" The elements are added to the compensation group setup on the **Budget cost elements** tab."},{"content":"Compensation groups can also determine the earning rates for a forecast position.","pos":[6724,6805]},{"content":"You set up a group to use either an hourly basis or an annual salary basis to calculate forecast position earnings.","pos":[6806,6921]},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Compensation rate tables<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab, a compensation grid of pay rates determines the earnings that are added to a forecast position, based on an assigned level and step.","pos":[6922,7095],"source":" On the **Compensation rate tables** tab, a compensation grid of pay rates determines the earnings that are added to a forecast position, based on an assigned level and step."},{"content":"These grids can be based on existing compensation grids in Human resources.","pos":[7096,7171]},{"content":"Alternatively, you can create new compensation grids for budget planning.","pos":[7172,7245]},{"content":"The effective dates and expiration dates on the compensation rate tables let you change pay rates on any date.","pos":[7248,7358]},{"content":"This feature is useful when a bargaining unit has negotiated for an across-the-board increase in the middle of a budget cycle.","pos":[7359,7485]},{"content":"In this case, you change the expiration date of the existing table to the day before the date of the rate change and add a new rate table that starts on the new date.","pos":[7486,7652]},{"content":"When you create a new rate table, if you select <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Create a new compensation grid from an existing grid<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, you can select an existing rate table from Human resources.","pos":[7653,7818],"source":" When you create a new rate table, if you select **Create a new compensation grid from an existing grid**, you can select an existing rate table from Human resources."},{"content":"On the rate table that is created, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Mass Change<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option lets you apply a percentage or flat amount increase or decrease to all rates in the grid.","pos":[7819,7970],"source":" On the rate table that is created, the **Mass Change** option lets you apply a percentage or flat amount increase or decrease to all rates in the grid."},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Increase schedule<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Date of increase<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> fields on the compensation group are used when you must create pay increases because positions go from one step to the next.","pos":[7973,8148],"source":"The **Increase schedule** and **Date of increase** fields on the compensation group are used when you must create pay increases because positions go from one step to the next."},{"content":"An annual pay increase is a typical scenario.","pos":[8149,8194]},{"content":"The increase schedule determines whether the position’s anniversary date or a single common date is used for the step increase.","pos":[8195,8322]},{"content":"The increase schedule applies to all forecast positions in the compensation group.","pos":[8323,8405]},{"content":"The earning cost element that is selected on the compensation group is used when you create earnings for the forecast positions in the group, including their base pay and any step increases.","pos":[8408,8598]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Compensation fixed plan<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field links the compensation group to a fixed compensation plan in Human resources.","pos":[8599,8714],"source":" The **Compensation fixed plan** field links the compensation group to a fixed compensation plan in Human resources."},{"content":"This link can assign a worker’s fixed compensation information to a forecast position, and can therefore make budget planning more accurate.","pos":[8715,8855]},{"content":"Remember that the structure of the compensation grid (the levels and steps) for the compensation group should match the structure of the fixed compensation plan.","pos":[8856,9017]},{"content":"Otherwise, the system can't correctly link the compensation group and the fixed compensation plan.","pos":[9018,9116]},{"pos":[9121,9148],"content":"Creating forecast positions","linkify":"Creating forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Creating forecast positions","pos":[0,27]}]},{"pos":[9149,9215],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>graphic3<ept id=\"p1\">](./media/graphic3-1024x327.png)](./media/graphic3.png)</ept>","source":"[![graphic3](./media/graphic3-1024x327.png)](./media/graphic3.png)"},{"pos":[9221,9271],"content":"Creating forecast positions for existing positions","linkify":"Creating forecast positions for existing positions","nodes":[{"content":"Creating forecast positions for existing positions","pos":[0,50]}]},{"content":"For the most accurate budget planning, you can create forecast positions by using details from existing positions in Microsoft Dynamics 365 for Operations, regardless of whether the position is currently filled or unfilled.","pos":[9273,9496]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add existing positions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function displays all the positions for an organization.","pos":[9499,9586],"source":"The **Add existing positions** function displays all the positions for an organization."},{"content":"By setting the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>As of<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> date, you can change the list of positions so that it contains the positions that existed at a date in the past or, more commonly, in the future (for example, the start of the next budget cycle).","pos":[9587,9807],"source":" By setting the **As of** date, you can change the list of positions so that it contains the positions that existed at a date in the past or, more commonly, in the future (for example, the start of the next budget cycle)."},{"content":"Select a budget planning process and budget plan scenario, select positions in the list, and then click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>OK<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to create forecast positions for the selected positions.","pos":[9808,9975],"source":" Select a budget planning process and budget plan scenario, select positions in the list, and then click **OK** to create forecast positions for the selected positions."},{"content":"Note that you can create only one forecast position for each existing position in a budget planning process and scenario.","pos":[9976,10097]},{"content":"However, you can create additional versions by assigning different budget plan scenarios.","pos":[10098,10187]},{"content":"If budget cost elements have been assigned to the position in Human resources, those budget cost elements are also assigned to the forecast position and use the default amounts.","pos":[10190,10367]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Assigned worker<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field on the forecast position is set to the name of the worker who is assigned to the position, if a worker is assigned.","pos":[10368,10513],"source":" The **Assigned worker** field on the forecast position is set to the name of the worker who is assigned to the position, if a worker is assigned."},{"content":"This field is a simple text field.","pos":[10514,10548]},{"content":"No direct link is created.","pos":[10549,10575]},{"content":"If a budget cost element is selected, the fixed compensation annual amount is assigned to the forecast position by using the selected cost element, provided that the assigned worker has a fixed compensation plan.","pos":[10578,10790]},{"content":"If the worker doesn't have a fixed comp plan, or if no worker is assigned, the default amount is used for the budget cost element.","pos":[10791,10921]},{"content":"When the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Assign a compensation group<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option is set to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Yes<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, if the worker who is assigned to the position has a step-based fixed compensation plan that is linked to a compensation group (as described earlier), the level and step from the worker are assigned to the forecast position, together with the compensation group.","pos":[10924,11252],"source":"When the **Assign a compensation group** option is set to **Yes**, if the worker who is assigned to the position has a step-based fixed compensation plan that is linked to a compensation group (as described earlier), the level and step from the worker are assigned to the forecast position, together with the compensation group."},{"content":"The earnings budget cost element from the compensation group is added to the forecast position, and the pay rate at the level and step from the compensation group are used.","pos":[11253,11425]},{"content":"The setting of the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Assign a compensation group<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option takes precedence over the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Budget cost element assignment<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> setting.","pos":[11428,11555],"source":"The setting of the **Assign a compensation group** option takes precedence over the **Budget cost element assignment** setting."},{"content":"The two settings can be used at the same time.","pos":[11556,11602]},{"pos":[11605,11662],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>graphic4<ept id=\"p1\">](./media/graphic4.png)](./media/graphic4.png)</ept>","source":"[![graphic4](./media/graphic4.png)](./media/graphic4.png)"},{"content":"Another option is to assign an anniversary date.","pos":[11665,11713]},{"content":"The selected date (adjusted start date, worker start date, employment start date, or seniority date) from the assigned worker is then set as the forecast position’s anniversary date, and is used for information and when pay increases are generated.","pos":[11714,11962]},{"pos":[11968,11999],"content":"Creating new forecast positions","linkify":"Creating new forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Creating new forecast positions","pos":[0,31]}]},{"content":"You can create new forecast positions in two ways: by copying an existing forecast position and by creating a completely new forecast position.","pos":[12001,12144]},{"content":"When a forecast position is selected, select <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Copy the selected forecast position<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to create a new forecast position that has a forecast state of <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Proposed<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[12147,12308],"source":"When a forecast position is selected, select **Copy the selected forecast position** to create a new forecast position that has a forecast state of **Proposed**."},{"content":"This forecast position has all of the same data as the forecast position that was copied, except the assigned worker and any notes on the budget cost elements.","pos":[12309,12468]},{"content":"Note that a corresponding new position is also created in Human resources.","pos":[12469,12543]},{"content":"This position has a description of <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Created by forecast<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[12544,12603],"source":" This position has a description of **Created by forecast**."},{"content":"You can also create a completely new forecast position.","pos":[12606,12661]},{"content":"Select an existing job, and also select the budget planning process and budget plan scenario.","pos":[12662,12755]},{"content":"You can then add any other details that you want to add.","pos":[12756,12812]},{"content":"Once again, a new position is created in Human resources at the same time.","pos":[12813,12887]},{"pos":[12892,12923],"content":"Working with forecast positions","linkify":"Working with forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Working with forecast positions","pos":[0,31]}]},{"pos":[12924,12990],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>graphic5<ept id=\"p1\">](./media/graphic5-1024x327.png)](./media/graphic5.png)</ept>","source":"[![graphic5](./media/graphic5-1024x327.png)](./media/graphic5.png)"},{"pos":[12996,13036],"content":"Multiple versions of a forecast position","linkify":"Multiple versions of a forecast position","nodes":[{"content":"Multiple versions of a forecast position","pos":[0,40]}]},{"content":"You can modify forecast positions either to apply known changes for the budget cycle or to model proposed changes.","pos":[13038,13152]},{"content":"A common practice is to create a baseline set of forecast positions, create copies of those forecast positions, and then use the copies to model different sets of changes.","pos":[13153,13324]},{"content":"The copies are assigned to a different budget plan scenario but, at least until changes are made, are otherwise identical to the forecast positions that they are copied from.","pos":[13325,13499]},{"content":"The originals and the copies share the same position in Human resources.","pos":[13500,13572]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Copy to scenario<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function provides this functionality.","pos":[13575,13637],"source":"The **Copy to scenario** function provides this functionality."},{"content":"Note that each Human resources position can have only one forecast position in each budget plan scenario.","pos":[13638,13743]},{"pos":[13749,13777],"content":"Modifying forecast positions","linkify":"Modifying forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Modifying forecast positions","pos":[0,28]}]},{"content":"Changes that are made to forecast positions are limited to those forecast positions.","pos":[13779,13863]},{"content":"The changes don't affect the position records in Human resources.","pos":[13864,13929]},{"content":"Most changes are also limited to the forecast position that is being edited.","pos":[13930,14006]},{"content":"In other words, the changes are specific to the budget planning process and budget plan scenario that are assigned.","pos":[14007,14122]},{"content":"The exceptions are changes to fields that are shared for the position across processes and scenarios.","pos":[14123,14224]},{"content":"These fields include the fields on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>General<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab and the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Financial dimensions<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab.","pos":[14225,14317],"source":" These fields include the fields on the **General** tab and the **Financial dimensions** tab."},{"content":"When these fields are changed, the new values apply to the position in all budget planning scenarios.","pos":[14318,14419]},{"content":"Therefore, these fields let you quickly update all versions.","pos":[14420,14480]},{"pos":[14487,14507],"content":"Budget cost elements","linkify":"Budget cost elements","nodes":[{"content":"Budget cost elements","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"Budget cost elements provide the main information for budget plans: the budget amount and the main account.","pos":[14509,14616]},{"content":"The budget amount is the amount that is sent to the budget plan when a forecast position is included in a plan.","pos":[14617,14728]},{"content":"The budget amount is calculated and can't be directly changed.","pos":[14729,14791]},{"content":"This amount is either the annual amount or a calculation of the percentage of the annual amount's basis elements (as defined on the setup of the budget cost element).","pos":[14792,14958]},{"content":"The amount is then factored by the number of days in the element’s date range (start date to end date) and also by the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Full-time equivalent<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (FTE) value for the forecast position.","pos":[14959,15141],"source":" The amount is then factored by the number of days in the element’s date range (start date to end date) and also by the **Full-time equivalent** (FTE) value for the forecast position."},{"pos":[15144,15358],"content":"For example, a budget cost element line from January 1, 2017, to June 30, 2017, that has an annual amount of 100,000 and an FTE value of <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>0.50<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is calculated as 100,000 × (181 days ÷ 365 days) × 0.50 = 24,794.52.","source":"For example, a budget cost element line from January 1, 2017, to June 30, 2017, that has an annual amount of 100,000 and an FTE value of **0.50** is calculated as 100,000 × (181 days ÷ 365 days) × 0.50 = 24,794.52."},{"content":"The budget cost element lines must be recalculated when the FTE value is changed on the forecast position.","pos":[15361,15467]},{"content":"The lines must also be recalculated when the activation dates or retirement dates are changed.","pos":[15468,15562]},{"content":"Changes to these dates can cause an update of the budget cost element's start and end dates, which must be within the forecast position’s dates.","pos":[15563,15707]},{"content":"When recalculation is required, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Recalculate<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> button becomes available, and a \"Requires calculation\" message is displayed.","pos":[15708,15836],"source":" When recalculation is required, the **Recalculate** button becomes available, and a \"Requires calculation\" message is displayed."},{"content":"Recalculation is also required if you add or remove a budget cost element.","pos":[15837,15911]},{"pos":[15913,15924],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Example<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Example**"},{"content":"The organization is considering two options for reducing the cost of an accountant position.","pos":[15927,16019]},{"content":"One option is to end the position part of the way through the year.","pos":[16020,16087]},{"content":"The other option is to change the position to half-time for the whole year.","pos":[16088,16163]},{"content":"Brad has created a forecast position for the existing accountant position in a baseline scenario.","pos":[16164,16261]},{"content":"He copies this baseline forecast position to scenario A, sets the retirement date to May 31, and recalculates.","pos":[16262,16372]},{"content":"Brad then copies the baseline forecast position to scenario B, changes the FTE value to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>0.50<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and recalculates.","pos":[16373,16488],"source":" Brad then copies the baseline forecast position to scenario B, changes the FTE value to **0.50**, and recalculates."},{"content":"Brad now has three versions, each of which has cost totals that are aligned with his options.","pos":[16489,16582]},{"pos":[16589,16619],"content":"Assigning a compensation group","linkify":"Assigning a compensation group","nodes":[{"content":"Assigning a compensation group","pos":[0,30]}]},{"content":"When you first assign a compensation group to a forecast position, the default budget cost elements from the compensation group are added.","pos":[16621,16759]},{"content":"If cost elements are already assigned to the forecast position, those cost elements remain.","pos":[16760,16851]},{"content":"If a compensation group has already been assigned and is being changed, the existing budget cost elements are removed and are replaced by the set from the compensation group.","pos":[16852,17026]},{"content":"When you select a compensation level and step, an earnings budget cost element (as defined in the compensation group) is added.","pos":[17029,17156]},{"content":"The annual amount is calculated by using the rate in the selected level and step, and the annual hours in the compensation group (or, for an annual based salary, the full amount in the level and step).","pos":[17157,17358]},{"content":"Once again, this amount is factored by the cost element line’s date range and the forecast position’s FTE value.","pos":[17359,17471]},{"pos":[17478,17498],"content":"Generating increases","linkify":"Generating increases","nodes":[{"content":"Generating increases","pos":[0,20]}]},{"content":"Annual increases (one per calendar year) can be created automatically for forecast positions that have a step-based compensation group assigned.","pos":[17500,17644]},{"content":"Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Generate increases<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to add an earnings budget cost element at the next highest step.","pos":[17645,17738],"source":" Click **Generate increases** to add an earnings budget cost element at the next highest step."},{"content":"The start date of the new earnings budget cost element is the scheduled increase date that is shown on the forecast position.","pos":[17739,17864]},{"content":"This date is set from the compensation group in one of two ways.","pos":[17865,17929]},{"content":"If the compensation group’s increase schedule is set to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Common date<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, the date of increase is specified on the compensation group.","pos":[17930,18063],"source":" If the compensation group’s increase schedule is set to **Common date**, the date of increase is specified on the compensation group."},{"content":"If the increase schedule is set to <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Anniversary date<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, the anniversary date field on the forecast position is used, and the budget cycle supplies the year.","pos":[18064,18221],"source":" If the increase schedule is set to **Anniversary date**, the anniversary date field on the forecast position is used, and the budget cycle supplies the year."},{"content":"If there are multiple calendar years in a budget cycle, multiple increases are added.","pos":[18222,18307]},{"content":"The end date of the current earnings budget cost element is updated with the day before the increase date.","pos":[18310,18416]},{"content":"The recalculation process is automatically used when increases are generated.","pos":[18417,18494]},{"content":"Therefore, you don't have to recalculate manually.","pos":[18495,18545]},{"content":"If you click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Generate increases<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> a second time, the process is run again but doesn't add more records.","pos":[18548,18653],"source":"If you click **Generate increases** a second time, the process is run again but doesn't add more records."},{"content":"Only one increase per calendar year is created.","pos":[18654,18701]},{"pos":[18708,18732],"content":"Changes from other pages","linkify":"Changes from other pages","nodes":[{"content":"Changes from other pages","pos":[0,24]}]},{"content":"Updates to forecast positions can also come from other areas, such as the budget cost element and the compensation group setup pages.","pos":[18734,18867]},{"content":"You can also modify forecast positions by using the mass update process.","pos":[18868,18940]},{"content":"Two options are available on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Budget 