ositions from an upper grid to a lower grid to include them in the update.","pos":[19689,19918],"source":" (Therefore, the **Update positions** page gives you a way to find out which forecast positions already have the cost element attached.) You move forecast positions from an upper grid to a lower grid to include them in the update."},{"content":"Note that the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Change dates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Cost calculation<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> tab immediately changes the budget cost element’s start and end dates on the forecast positions.","pos":[19921,20085],"source":"Note that the **Change dates** function on the **Cost calculation** tab immediately changes the budget cost element’s start and end dates on the forecast positions."},{"content":"No selection options are available.","pos":[20086,20121]},{"content":"On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Compensation group<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Update position rates<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> function applies the current compensation rate table rates to forecast positions that are assigned to the group.","pos":[20124,20302],"source":"On the **Compensation group** page, the **Update position rates** function applies the current compensation rate table rates to forecast positions that are assigned to the group."},{"content":"The rates are updated, and additional cost element lines are added for any new rate table lines (based on dates).","pos":[20303,20416]},{"content":"However, the budget cost elements and the increase dates aren't updated.","pos":[20417,20489]},{"content":"You can select which budget planning process and budget plan scenario to update.","pos":[20490,20570]},{"content":"Therefore, you can update one scenario but leave other scenarios unchanged for comparison.","pos":[20571,20661]},{"content":"By selecting forecast positions and then clicking <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Mass update<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, you can add or change more than one forecast position at that same time.","pos":[20664,20803],"source":"By selecting forecast positions and then clicking **Mass update**, you can add or change more than one forecast position at that same time."},{"content":"Many options are available.","pos":[20804,20831]},{"content":"One option on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Financial dimensions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab differs slightly from the others and is related to budget cost elements.","pos":[20832,20951],"source":" One option on the **Financial dimensions** tab differs slightly from the others and is related to budget cost elements."},{"content":"You can add budget cost elements by setting the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Budget defaults<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Yes<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[20952,21038],"source":" You can add budget cost elements by setting the **Budget defaults** option to **Yes**."},{"content":"If no budget cost elements are selected, but <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Budget defaults<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is set to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Yes<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, all budget cost elements that are currently assigned are removed.","pos":[21039,21188],"source":" If no budget cost elements are selected, but **Budget defaults** is set to **Yes**, all budget cost elements that are currently assigned are removed."},{"content":"The recalculation process is automatically used on any forecast position that has changed.","pos":[21191,21281]},{"pos":[21286,21331],"content":"Bringing forecast positions into budget plans","linkify":"Bringing forecast positions into budget plans","nodes":[{"content":"Bringing forecast positions into budget plans","pos":[0,45]}]},{"pos":[21333,21399],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>graphic6<ept id=\"p1\">](./media/graphic6-1024x327.png)](./media/graphic6.png)</ept>","source":"[![graphic6](./media/graphic6-1024x327.png)](./media/graphic6.png)"},{"content":"The purpose of creating and modifying forecast positions is to add them to budget plans, so that the budget plans include the most accurate budget amounts.","pos":[21401,21556]},{"content":"There are two methods for adding forecast positions to budget plans.","pos":[21557,21625]},{"content":"You can use either a generation process or a selection process on the budget plan.","pos":[21626,21708]},{"pos":[21714,21762],"content":"Generating a budget plan from forecast positions","linkify":"Generating a budget plan from forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Generating a budget plan from forecast positions","pos":[0,48]}]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Generate budget plan from forecast positions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function creates or updates budget plans so that they have the budget amounts and FTE counts from forecast positions.","pos":[21764,21934],"source":"The **Generate budget plan from forecast positions** function creates or updates budget plans so that they have the budget amounts and FTE counts from forecast positions."},{"content":"The budget amounts from the forecast position become the budget plan line amounts and are aggregated by financial dimension values and effective date.","pos":[21935,22085]},{"content":"The generation process assigns the source forecast position to the budget plan line.","pos":[22086,22170]},{"content":"To view the position, you can either add the forecast position as a row in the budget plan layout or use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Budget plan lines<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> inquiry.","pos":[22171,22310],"source":" To view the position, you can either add the forecast position as a row in the budget plan layout or use the **Budget plan lines** inquiry."},{"content":"To skip this assignment, set the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Include position in budget plan line<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option to <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>No<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.","pos":[22311,22402],"source":" To skip this assignment, set the **Include position in budget plan line** option to **No**."},{"content":"You can select a budget plan FTE scenario to include the number of FTEs in the budget plan.","pos":[22405,22496]},{"content":"You can select only scenarios of the quantity type that are included in the layout of the target budget plan.","pos":[22497,22606]},{"content":"When you select an FTE scenario is, you must also specify an FTE main account.","pos":[22607,22685]},{"content":"This account is used to create the quantity budget plan lines.","pos":[22686,22748]},{"content":"The budget planning process and budget plan scenario that are selected in the source determine the target scenario budget planning process and scenario.","pos":[22751,22903]},{"content":"Because these attributes are assigned to forecast positions, they must be in synchronized with the budget plan.","pos":[22904,23015]},{"content":"Therefore, the attributes can't be edited on the target.","pos":[23016,23072]},{"content":"As for other generation processes, three options are available:","pos":[23075,23138]},{"pos":[23144,23261],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Create a new budget plan<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – Create a new plan that has the attributes that are selected in the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Target<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> section.","source":"**Create a new budget plan** – Create a new plan that has the attributes that are selected in the **Target** section."},{"pos":[23266,23460],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Replace the existing budget plan scenario<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – Delete all data in the target budget plan in the selected budget plan scenario and create new lines that have the selected forecast position data.","source":"**Replace the existing budget plan scenario** – Delete all data in the target budget plan in the selected budget plan scenario and create new lines that have the selected forecast position data."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Update the existing budget plan scenario, and append new data<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – Update existing lines in the target plan that match the source lines, and also add new lines for new data.","pos":[23465,23639],"source":"**Update the existing budget plan scenario, and append new data** – Update existing lines in the target plan that match the source lines, and also add new lines for new data."},{"content":"The matching is based on the ledger account, date, budget class, and other values, such as the forecast position.","pos":[23640,23753]},{"content":"All lines that have a position number that matches the source position number are replaced with the new lines from the source.","pos":[23754,23880]},{"pos":[23886,23914],"content":"Selecting forecast positions","linkify":"Selecting forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Selecting forecast positions","pos":[0,28]}]},{"content":"You can also add forecast position budget amounts directly to a budget plan.","pos":[23916,23992]},{"content":"Use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add positions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function above the budget plan lines to select the forecast positions to include.","pos":[23993,24100],"source":" Use the **Add positions** function above the budget plan lines to select the forecast positions to include."},{"content":"The budget plan scenarios that you can select as the source are limited to scenarios that are included in the plan’s layout.","pos":[24103,24227]},{"content":"One option on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Target<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab lets you specify that the FTE scenario and main account are available to include FTE counts, but aren't required.","pos":[24228,24374],"source":" One option on the **Target** tab lets you specify that the FTE scenario and main account are available to include FTE counts, but aren't required."},{"content":"This selection process behaves like the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Update existing budget plan scenario, and append new data<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option for a generation process.","pos":[24377,24511],"source":"This selection process behaves like the **Update existing budget plan scenario, and append new data** option for a generation process."},{"content":"All existing budget plan lines where the forecast position is being added are removed and replaced by new lines that are based on the current state of the forecast position.","pos":[24512,24685]},{"pos":[24692,24704],"content":"Date options","linkify":"Date options","nodes":[{"content":"Date options","pos":[0,12]}]},{"content":"For both the generation process and the selection process, the start date on the budget cost element line determines the effective date of the corresponding budget plan line.","pos":[24706,24880]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Allocation method<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> field on the budget cost element setup page specifies the allocation method:","pos":[24881,24983],"source":" The **Allocation method** field on the budget cost element setup page specifies the allocation method:"},{"pos":[24989,25092],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Start date<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – The budget cost element's start date is used as the budget plan line's effective date.","source":"**Start date** – The budget cost element's start date is used as the budget plan line's effective date."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Monthly<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – The budget amount is evenly divided by the number of months in the date range to produce a typical monthly amount that is assigned on the first day of each month.","pos":[25097,25273],"source":"**Monthly** – The budget amount is evenly divided by the number of months in the date range to produce a typical monthly amount that is assigned on the first day of each month."},{"content":"If the first period is a partial month, the amount for that month is factored by the number of days that the cost is active in that month, and the result is assigned to the start date.","pos":[25274,25458]},{"content":"The amount for the last month is the difference between the total budget amount and the sum of all other months.","pos":[25459,25571]},{"content":"Therefore, rounding might affect the amount for the last month.","pos":[25572,25635]},{"pos":[25640,25750],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Quarterly<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – This method is the same as <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Monthly<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, but the calculations are done for three-month periods.","source":"**Quarterly** – This method is the same as **Monthly**, but the calculations are done for three-month periods."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Weekly<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – The logic resembles the logic of the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Monthly<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Quarterly<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> methods.","pos":[25755,25843],"source":"**Weekly** – The logic resembles the logic of the **Monthly** and **Quarterly** methods."},{"content":"The budget amount is evenly divided by the number of weeks in the date range to produce a typical weekly amount that is assigned on the first day of each week.","pos":[25844,26003]},{"content":"If the first period is a partial week, the amount for that week is factored by the number of days that the cost is active in that week, and the result is assigned to the start date.","pos":[26004,26185]},{"content":"The amount for the last week is the difference between the total budget amount and the sum of all other weeks.","pos":[26186,26296]},{"content":"Therefore, rounding might affect the amount for the last week.","pos":[26297,26359]},{"pos":[26364,26469],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Biweekly<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – This method is the same as <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Weekly<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, but the calculations are done for two-week periods.","source":"**Biweekly** – This method is the same as **Weekly**, but the calculations are done for two-week periods."},{"pos":[26476,26531],"content":"Changing budget plan lines that have forecast positions","linkify":"Changing budget plan lines that have forecast positions","nodes":[{"content":"Changing budget plan lines that have forecast positions","pos":[0,55]}]},{"content":"Budget plan lines show the source of the budget amounts (the forecast position number) but aren't linked.","pos":[26533,26638]},{"content":"Therefore, changes to the forecast position aren't shown on the budget plan line, and changes to the budget plan line are shown in the forecast position.","pos":[26639,26792]},{"content":"If you change a forecast position and want the updates to be included in a budget plan, you must bring the forecast position into the plan again.","pos":[26793,26938]},{"content":"However, remember that this process removes all lines where that forecast position is assigned.","pos":[26939,27034]},{"content":"Therefore, any changes that you've made to those lines are removed.","pos":[27035,27102]},{"content":"To see which budget plans a forecast position has been included in, you can generate the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Forecast positions by budget plan<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> report.","pos":[27105,27239],"source":"To see which budget plans a forecast position has been included in, you can generate the **Forecast positions by budget plan** report."},{"content":"Alternatively, on the forecast position, you can open the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Associated budget plans<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> FactBox to view the plans.","pos":[27240,27352],"source":" Alternatively, on the forecast position, you can open the **Associated budget plans** FactBox to view the plans."}]}